modules.description: This module defines element types and memory layouts for typed multi-dimensional arrays, enabling precise control over data representation and memory ordering. It provides utilities to convert between generic and dimension-specific array types (0D–3D) while preserving element counts and storage characteristics, supporting operations like reshaping and cross-language data interchange. These features are particularly useful for handling binary data with strict type or layout requirements, such as numerical computations or interfacing with C/Fortran libraries.
